---
title: "Data types"
format: revealjs
---





# Why should you care about data types?

## Example: Cat lovers

A survey asked respondents their name and number of cats. The instructions said to enter the number of cats as a numerical value.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
cat_lovers <- read_csv("data/cat-lovers.csv")
cat_lovers
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 60 × 2
   name           number_of_cats
   <chr>          <chr>         
 1 Bernice Warren 0             
 2 Woodrow Stone  0             
 3 Willie Bass    1             
 4 Tyrone Estrada 3             
 5 Alex Daniels   3             
 6 Jane Bates     2             
 7 Latoya Simpson 1             
 8 Darin Woods    1             
 9 Agnes Cobb     0             
10 Tabitha Grant  0             
# ℹ 50 more rows
```


:::
:::



## Oh why won't you work?!



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
cat_lovers |>
  summarize(mean_cats = mean(number_of_cats))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Warning: There was 1 warning in `summarize()`.
ℹ In argument: `mean_cats = mean(number_of_cats)`.
Caused by warning in `mean.default()`:
! argument is not numeric or logical: returning NA
```


:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 1 × 1
  mean_cats
      <dbl>
1        NA
```


:::
:::



## Let's read the docs!



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
?mean
```
:::



![](images/mean-docs.gif){fig-alt="Documentation for the mean function."}

## Oh why won't you still work??!!



::: {.cell output-location='fragment'}

```{.r .cell-code}
cat_lovers |>
  summarize(mean_cats = mean(number_of_cats, na.rm = TRUE))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Warning: There was 1 warning in `summarize()`.
ℹ In argument: `mean_cats = mean(number_of_cats, na.rm =
  TRUE)`.
Caused by warning in `mean.default()`:
! argument is not numeric or logical: returning NA
```


:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 1 × 1
  mean_cats
      <dbl>
1        NA
```


:::
:::



## Take a breath and look at your data

::: task
What is the type of the `number_of_cats` variable?
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
glimpse(cat_lovers)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
Rows: 60
Columns: 2
$ name           <chr> "Bernice Warren", "Woodrow Stone", …
$ number_of_cats <chr> "0", "0", "1", "3", "3", "2", "1", …
```


:::
:::



